President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate two individuals to key positions in his administration. 

The first nominee is David Stilwell of Hawaii, who is being considered for the position of Assistant Secretary of State for East Asian and Pacific Affairs at the Department of State. Stilwell is an Air Force veteran with over 35 years of experience as a pilot, commander, and Korean linguist. He currently serves as the Director of the China Strategic Focus Group at the U.S. Indo-Pacific Command Headquarters in Hawaii and is also an Adjunct Senior Fellow at the East West Center in Honolulu. Stilwell has previously held positions such as Staff Officer for Joint Staff Plans and Policy (Asia) at the Pentagon and Defense Attach√© at the U.S. Embassy in Beijing. He holds multiple degrees, including a B.S. from the U.S. Air Force Academy and M.A. degrees from the University of Hawaii at Manoa, U.S. Air Command and Staff College, and the U.S. Army War College. Stilwell has received the Department of Defense Superior Service Award and is fluent in Korean, Chinese, and limited Japanese.

The second nominee is Mary Catherine Phee of Illinois, who is being considered for the position of Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the State of Qatar. Phee is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as the Deputy Special Representative for Afghanistan Reconciliation at the Department of State. She has previously held positions such as Ambassador to the Republic of South Sudan, Principal Deputy Assistant Secretary of the Bureau of International Organization Affairs, Deputy Chief of Mission of the U.S. Embassy in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia, and Director for Iraq on the National Security Council. Phee has received a B.A. from Indiana University and an M.A.L.D. from the Fletcher School of Law and Diplomacy at Tufts University. She has been recognized with awards such as the State Department's Robert C. Frasure Memorial Award, the Baker-Wilkins Award for Outstanding Deputy Chief of Mission, the Secretary of Defense Meritorious Civilian Service Award, and the Order of the British Empire. Phee is fluent in Arabic.